What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it, but only if you want to major in classics. If you don't want to, your time is better spent in a translation class.

I would not recommend taking this class unless it is a requirement for your major (i.e., Classics), and I would not recommend taking it until at least your sophomore year. You will most likely not be prepared.

This is an intense course. Your Latin will improve, but you have to work very hard. If you are a freshman, I would recommend waiting until you have a few semesters if college Latin under your belt before taking this class.
